This is a collection of roles to install and validate software-factory.

check-firehose-events
---------------------
When firehose is enabled, check if data are present in log files.

configure-fqdn
--------------
Set fqdn in sfconfig.yaml and configure instance hostname.

configure-sfconfig
------------------
Configure arch.yaml and sfconfig.yaml.

fetch-artifacts
---------------
Collect job artifacts.

fetch-instance-status
---------------------
Get instance data (mount point).

finish-test
-----------
Collect log files and ara data.

install-mirrors
---------------
Install yum repositories (stable and master) and local build mirrors.

install-sfconfig
----------------
Install and update sf-config package.

prepare-test-env
----------------
Remove unused directories created by DIB, create artifacts directory and set artifacts variable.

restore-ci-repo
---------------
Restore build repo files and force sf-release to to master.

run-backup-create
-----------------
Create backup.

run-checker
-----------
Run checker.py.

run-erase
---------
Erase sf deployment.

run-firehose-listener
---------------------
Install and run mosquitto if firehose in arch.yaml.

run-functional-tests
--------------------
Run functional tests.

run-health-check
----------------
Run health-check playbook.

run-provisioner
---------------
Run data provisionner.

run-sfconfig
------------
Run sfconfig.

setup-test-env
--------------
Install python-nose packages.

update-bootstrap-mode
---------------------
Allow sf_user to access to software factory data (etc, var).

update-system
-------------
Update all packages on the instance.